- read rss feeds like good ol' googlereads
    [x] figure out what open source projects exists for using as an RSS reader
        - top self-hosted web apps (google reader-like)
            - FreshRSS (~14.3k stars, PHP)
                most popular, google reader API, handles 100k+ articles
                https://github.com/FreshRSS/FreshRSS
            - Miniflux (~8.9k stars, Go)
                minimalist, single binary, fast and lean
                https://github.com/miniflux/v2
            - NewsBlur (~6.7k stars, Python/Django)
                intelligence/training features, social reading, heavy infra
                https://github.com/samuelclay/NewsBlur
            - CommaFeed (~3.4k stars, Java/React)
                closest UI to original google reader, lightweight
                https://github.com/Athou/commafeed
            - Feedbin (~3.5k stars, Ruby on Rails)
                polished, newsletter + podcast support, complex self-hosting
                https://github.com/feedbin/feedbin
            - Stringer (~4k stars, Ruby/Sinatra)
                anti-social, minimalist, heroku-deployable
                https://github.com/stringer-rss/stringer
            - Fusion (~1.7k stars, Go/Svelte)
                newer, ~80MB memory, single binary
                https://github.com/0x2E/fusion
            - Selfoss (~2.4k stars, PHP)
                lightweight, multipurpose aggregator, maintenance mode
                https://github.com/fossar/selfoss
            - Tiny Tiny RSS (PHP)
                retired Nov 2025, community fork exists
                https://github.com/tt-rss/tt-rss
        - desktop apps
            - NetNewsWire (~9.4k stars, macOS/iOS only)
                https://github.com/Ranchero-Software/NetNewsWire
            - Fluent Reader (~8.9k stars, Win/Mac/Linux)
                https://github.com/yang991178/fluent-reader
            - Newsboat (~3.6k stars, terminal CLI)
                https://github.com/newsboat/newsboat
        - libraries for building your own
            - gofeed (Go) - universal RSS/Atom/JSON parser
                https://github.com/mmcdole/gofeed
            - feedparser (Python) - classic python feed parser
                https://github.com/kurtmckee/feedparser
        - best picks for google reader experience
            1. CommaFeed - closest to original google reader UI
            2. FreshRSS - best all-around (most features, best mobile client support)
            3. Miniflux - best for minimalism and speed
        - self-hosting requirements
            - easiest (single container, no external DB)
                - Fusion: 1 container, embedded SQLite, ~50MB RAM
                    docker run -p 8080:8080 -v $(pwd)/fusion:/data -e FUSION_PASSWORD="pass" ghcr.io/0x2e/fusion:latest
                - CommaFeed: 1 container, embedded H2 DB, ~128-256MB RAM
                    docker run -p 8082:8082 athou/commafeed
                - FreshRSS: 1 container, SQLite default, ~128MB RAM
                    docker run -p 8080:80 -e 'CRON_MIN=1,31' -v freshrss_data:/var/www/FreshRSS/data freshrss/freshrss
            - easy (needs PostgreSQL)
                - Miniflux: 2 containers (app + postgres), ~64MB RAM + PG
                - Stringer: 3 containers (setup + app + postgres), ~256MB RAM + PG
            - medium (no docker)
                - Selfoss: bare PHP, SQLite default, ~64MB RAM, needs PHP web server + cron
            - hard (heavy infrastructure)
                - NewsBlur: 11-12 containers, PG + MongoDB + Redis + Elasticsearch, 2-4GB RAM
                - Feedbin: 11+ containers, PG + Redis + ES + Memcached + Minio, 2+GB RAM, no official self-host support
    [x] local setup requirements
        - prerequisites: just Docker (already installed, v28.2.2)
        - no domain, SSL, or reverse proxy needed for local use
        - quick start commands (run one, then open in browser)
            - Fusion (simplest, ~50MB RAM)
                docker run -d -p 8080:8080 -v fusion:/data -e FUSION_PASSWORD="yourpassword" ghcr.io/0x2e/fusion:latest
                open http://localhost:8080
            - CommaFeed (closest to Google Reader, ~128MB RAM)
                docker run -d -p 8082:8082 -v commafeed:/commafeed/data athou/commafeed
                open http://localhost:8082
            - FreshRSS (most features, ~128MB RAM)
                docker run -d -p 8080:80 -e 'CRON_MIN=1,31' -v freshrss_data:/var/www/FreshRSS/data freshrss/freshrss
                open http://localhost:8080
